=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Tutorials_07-Mix-it-Up_ex4 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark mixed sound, with complex characteristics, featuring instant attack and compressed envelope, with static spectral movement, filtered with highpass character, and spectrally dense.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: instant
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: compressed
  envelope_flatness: very_dynamic
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: mixed
  spectral_complexity_mean: dense
  spectral_flux_normalized: static
  spectral_slope: highpass
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 0.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: 0.0000
  harmonic_regularity: 0.0000
  pitch_clarity: 0.0000
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: 0.0000
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: 07. Mix it Up Example 4
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Tutorials/Getting-Started/07-Mix-it-Up.html
// Tags: 07-Mix-it-Up, Tutorials
// ---
// --- Example 4 ---
// Look at the post window for frequencies and indices
(
    var n = 8;
    {
        Mix.fill(n, { arg index;
            var freq;
            index.postln;
            freq = 440 + index;
            freq.postln;
            SinOsc.ar(freq , 0, 1 / n)
        })
    }.play;
)
